<p>I&#8217;ve now had three trips in my camper van. I&#8217;m extremely pleased with the van itself. The only downside is that it&#8217;s a bit thirsty on fuel. I guess that&#8217;s no surprise being four wheel drive with a three litre V6 engine. It&#8217;s very nice to drive though, with decent acceleration for a heavy vehicle.&nbsp;</p>
<p><img data-attachment-id="12113" data-permalink="https://blogpackinglight.wordpress.com/2017/02/12/more-camper-van-paraphernalia/img_2998/" data-orig-file="https://blogpackinglight.files.wordpress.com/2017/02/img_2998.jpg?w=474" data-orig-size="522,522" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}" data-image-title="img_2998" data-image-description="" data-medium-file="https://blogpackinglight.files.wordpress.com/2017/02/img_2998.jpg?w=474?w=300" data-large-file="https://blogpackinglight.files.wordpress.com/2017/02/img_2998.jpg?w=474?w=474"   alt="" src="https://blogpackinglight.files.wordpress.com/2017/02/img_2998.jpg?w=474" title="" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-12113" srcset="https://blogpackinglight.files.wordpress.com/2017/02/img_2998.jpg?w=474 474w, https://blogpackinglight.files.wordpress.com/2017/02/img_2998.jpg?w=150 150w, https://blogpackinglight.files.wordpress.com/2017/02/img_2998.jpg?w=300 300w, https://blogpackinglight.files.wordpress.com/2017/02/img_2998.jpg 522w" sizes="(max-width: 474px) 100vw, 474px">I&#8217;ve been looking for a couple of compact deck chairs. I looked at some Helinox ones but balked at the price. However, I found some almost identical ones on Amazon for a third of the price, so I took a punt. I don&#8217;t really like buying cheap copies, but I have to say, these are decent quality. They are decently comfortable to sit in and fold down really small. For a camper van the size of mine, you have to be careful not to have bulky gear otherwise it eats up the storage space. If you&#8217;re interested, look up Moon Lence on Amazon and you&#8217;ll find them. There are actually even cheaper chairs, but none on Amazon Prime.&nbsp;</p>
<p><img data-attachment-id="12115" data-permalink="https://blogpackinglight.wordpress.com/2017/02/12/more-camper-van-paraphernalia/img_3041/" data-orig-file="https://blogpackinglight.files.wordpress.com/2017/02/img_3041.jpg?w=474" data-orig-size="522,348" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}" data-image-title="img_3041" data-image-description="" data-medium-file="https://blogpackinglight.files.wordpress.com/2017/02/img_3041.jpg?w=474?w=300" data-large-file="https://blogpackinglight.files.wordpress.com/2017/02/img_3041.jpg?w=474?w=474"   alt="" src="https://blogpackinglight.files.wordpress.com/2017/02/img_3041.jpg?w=474" title="" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-12115" srcset="https://blogpackinglight.files.wordpress.com/2017/02/img_3041.jpg?w=474 474w, https://blogpackinglight.files.wordpress.com/2017/02/img_3041.jpg?w=150 150w, https://blogpackinglight.files.wordpress.com/2017/02/img_3041.jpg?w=300 300w, https://blogpackinglight.files.wordpress.com/2017/02/img_3041.jpg 522w" sizes="(max-width: 474px) 100vw, 474px"><br />
I was so impressed with the chairs, that I bought a folding table as well. Again, I am impressed with the quality. It will certainly be civilised to be able to sit outside quaffing a (non alcholic) cocktail and munching a few select morsels. This table no longer appears to be available, but the are similar ones around.&nbsp;</p>
<p><img data-attachment-id="12117" data-permalink="https://blogpackinglight.wordpress.com/2017/02/12/more-camper-van-paraphernalia/img_3040/" data-orig-file="https://blogpackinglight.files.wordpress.com/2017/02/img_3040.jpg?w=474" data-orig-size="696,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}" data-image-title="img_3040" data-image-description="" data-medium-file="https://blogpackinglight.files.wordpress.com/2017/02/img_3040.jpg?w=474?w=209" data-large-file="https://blogpackinglight.files.wordpress.com/2017/02/img_3040.jpg?w=474?w=474"   alt="" src="https://blogpackinglight.files.wordpress.com/2017/02/img_3040.jpg?w=474" title="" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-12117" srcset="https://blogpackinglight.files.wordpress.com/2017/02/img_3040.jpg?w=474 474w, https://blogpackinglight.files.wordpress.com/2017/02/img_3040.jpg?w=104 104w, https://blogpackinglight.files.wordpress.com/2017/02/img_3040.jpg?w=209 209w, https://blogpackinglight.files.wordpress.com/2017/02/img_3040.jpg 696w" sizes="(max-width: 474px) 100vw, 474px"></p>
<p>Next up is a hose. I&#8217;ve not bothered to use the on board water tank as it&#8217;s a bit of a fiddle to fill and I&#8217;d rather use a 6L Platypus container for drinking water. However, it might be useful to have some running water for washing etc. If you&#8217;re on a campsite, you&#8217;re going to need a hose to fill up the tank. I&#8217;ve been looking at normal hoses, but they are quite bulky. You can get flat hoses, but they are a bit of a fiddle to rewind. Enter the XHose, which I spotted in Robert Dyas. The XHose stretches to three times its original length. It seemed a good solution, so I&#8217;ve bought one. I&#8217;ve not tried it out, but it looks ideal for occasionally using on campsites. I bought the 50ft one. It&#8217;s quite compact for storage.&nbsp;</p>
<p><img data-attachment-id="12119" data-permalink="https://blogpackinglight.wordpress.com/2017/02/12/more-camper-van-paraphernalia/img_3043/" data-orig-file="https://blogpackinglight.files.wordpress.com/2017/02/img_3043.jpg?w=474" data-orig-size="300,244" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}" data-image-title="img_3043" data-image-description="" data-medium-file="https://blogpackinglight.files.wordpress.com/2017/02/img_3043.jpg?w=474?w=300" data-large-file="https://blogpackinglight.files.wordpress.com/2017/02/img_3043.jpg?w=474?w=300"   alt="" src="https://blogpackinglight.files.wordpress.com/2017/02/img_3043.jpg?w=474" title="" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-12119" srcset="https://blogpackinglight.files.wordpress.com/2017/02/img_3043.jpg 300w, https://blogpackinglight.files.wordpress.com/2017/02/img_3043.jpg?w=150 150w" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px"><br />
Lastly, before my last trip I bought a cheapo windscreen frost protector from Amazon marketplace. It&#8217;s a bit like radiator insulation. It lasted one trip before the wind trashed it. Amazingly I found a dedicated screen protector on <a href="http://www.ebay.co.uk/itm/Toyota-Alphard-Vellfire-Black-Screen-Cover-Blind-Camping-Sun-Frost-Protection-/122206359425?hash=item1c74110f81:g:ULkAAOSwnbZYF22W">eBay for an Alphard&nbsp;</a>. It&#8217;s much better quality, so hopefully this one will work. It&#8217;s not padded, so it won&#8217;t insulate, but it should protect from frost, which is primarily what I wanted it for.&nbsp;</p><br />  <a rel="nofollow" href="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/gocomments/blogpackinglight.wordpress.com/12112/"><img alt="" border="0" src="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/comments/blogpackinglight.wordpress.com/12112/" /></a> <img alt="" border="0" src="https://pixel.wp.com/b.gif?host=blogpackinglight.wordpress.com&#038;blog=2188128&#038;post=12112&#038;subd=blogpackinglight&#038;ref=&#038;feed=1" width="1" height="1" />